UPDATE sops SET content = E'# Vektiss Team SOP\n\n**Sales, onboarding, production, approvals, and monthly optimization workflow**\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nStandardize the client experience from sales call to monthly content delivery and optimization.\n\n## Use\n\nInternal team alignment, client onboarding, portal setup, and scope clarity.\n\nThis document standardizes how the Vektiss team handles a content client from first conversation through recurring delivery. Use it as the operating reference for sales, onboarding, project management, production, and approvals.\n\n---\n\n## Quick Reference\n\n| Key Item | Standard |\n|---|---|\n| Core package | <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">16 videos per month</span>; <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">1 two-hour virtual shoot</span> |\n| Revision rule | <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">One round</span> per monthly batch; client sends <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">one consolidated list within 24 hours</span> |\n| Posting rule | <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">No approval, no posting</span> |\n| Communication home | <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">Vektiss portal</span> |\n| Email support | Mon–Fri, 9:00 AM–5:00 PM; respond <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">within 24 hours</span> |\n| Reschedule policy | <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">$75 fee</span> with less than 24 hours notice |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Discovery Call SOP\n\n- Open with rapport: ask how their day or week is going.\n- Ask how they got into what they do. Listen for <span style=\"color:#3b82f6;font-weight:600\">story, credibility, pain points, and motivators</span>.\n- Ask what they are looking for with content and why they reached out to Vektiss.\n- Explain what Vektiss does and <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">state whether their needs align with the offer</span>.\n- Ask about <span style=\"color:#3b82f6;font-weight:600\">goals and desired outcomes</span>.\n- Ask what is currently <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">stopping them from reaching those goals</span>.\n- Present the offer in the context of what they shared.\n- Show proof or relevant examples when helpful.\n- Ask <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">when they are ready to get started</span>.\n- Handle <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">questions, objections, and decision timing</span>.\n\n> <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">✅ IF QUALIFIED:</span> Their needs align, they have budget, and they are ready → move to **Section 3: Closing Workflow**\n>\n> <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">❌ IF NOT QUALIFIED:</span> Needs don''t align, no budget, or not ready → document the lead, set a follow-up date, and move to nurture sequence. Do not force the offer.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Core Offer\n\n- **3-Month Short-Form Content System:** <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">$5,800 paid in full</span>\n- **Month-to-month option:** <span style=\"color:#3b82f6;font-weight:600\">$2,500</span>\n- **Monthly deliverables:** <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">16 short-form videos</span>, 1 two-hour virtual shoot, research, scripting, editing, captions, posting, analytics review, strategy call, and optimization\n\n---\n\n## 3. Closing Workflow\n\n- <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">If the client says yes</span> → send the contract immediately.\n- Send the invoice or payment link.\n- Once <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">signed and paid</span> → send a copy of the contract and <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">activate portal access</span>.\n- Prompt the client to <span style=\"color:#3b82f6;font-weight:600\">book the onboarding call</span>.\n- Run a quick social-platform analysis and note obvious gaps or opportunities.\n\n> <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">⚠️ IF CLIENT HESITATES:</span> Answer questions, address objections, give them space. Never pressure. Set a follow-up within 48 hours.\n>\n> <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">❌ IF CLIENT DECLINES:</span> Thank them, document the reason, add to follow-up list for 30/60/90 day check-in.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Portal & Communication Rules\n\n- All client communication should be routed through the <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">Vektiss portal</span> whenever possible.\n- Use the portal for questions, revision collection, status updates, approvals, and deliverable tracking.\n- Clients receive <span style=\"color:#3b82f6;font-weight:600\">email notifications</span> from portal activity.\n- Email support window: Monday through Friday, 9:00 AM to 5:00 PM.\n- Response expectation: <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">within 24 hours</span> on business days.\n- Each client should also know who their <span style=\"color:#3b82f6;font-weight:600\">project manager</span> is.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Onboarding Call SOP\n\n- Review what the client is currently doing with content.\n- Confirm <span style=\"color:#3b82f6;font-weight:600\">platforms in use</span> and any login or access requirements.\n- Collect <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">logos, branding, offers, CTAs, and existing assets</span>.\n- Determine <span style=\"color:#3b82f6;font-weight:600\">tone, audience, content pillars, and content priorities</span>.\n- Ask whether they already use a scheduler or content-management process.\n- <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">Document everything</span> in the project record.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Pre-Production SOP\n\n- Complete <span style=\"color:#3b82f6;font-weight:600\">platform analysis</span> and recommend content direction.\n- Build the <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">monthly game plan</span> from goals, audience pain points, and offers.\n- <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">Write scripts before</span> the shoot is scheduled or finalized.\n- Send the client a <span style=\"color:#3b82f6;font-weight:600\">prep checklist</span> and upload instructions.\n- Confirm the <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">two-hour virtual shoot date</span>.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Client Shoot Requirements\n\n- <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">Quiet room, clean background, enough phone storage, second screen, microphone, light, and stable internet.</span>\n- Client should be ready to record <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">16 videos</span> during the guided session.\n- Provide upload link for Dropbox or Google Drive.\n\n> <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">⚠️ IF CLIENT IS NOT PREPARED:</span> Do not proceed with the shoot. Reschedule and apply the <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">$75 rescheduling fee</span> if within 24 hours.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Production & Delivery SOP\n\n- Run the two-hour virtual shoot and guide the client through the scripts.\n- Receive footage and <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">confirm file integrity</span>.\n- Send videos in batches, with the <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">first four delivered within three days</span>.\n- Continue rolling delivery until the monthly set is complete.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Revision & Approval SOP\n\n- <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">One round of revisions</span> per monthly batch.\n- Client must review the batch together and submit <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">one consolidated revision list within 24 hours</span>.\n- <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">Do not post unapproved content.</span>\n- <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">Delayed review shifts the publishing timeline</span> and should be noted in the portal.\n\n> <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">✅ IF APPROVED:</span> Move to **Section 10: Publishing & Optimization**\n>\n> <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">⚠️ IF REVISIONS REQUESTED:</span> Complete the one round, resubmit, and wait for final approval before posting.\n>\n> <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">❌ IF NO RESPONSE WITHIN 24 HOURS:</span> Flag in portal, notify PM, and shift timeline. Do not post.\n\n---\n\n## 10. Publishing & Optimization SOP\n\n- Once <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">approved</span>, schedule the content at the agreed consistent posting time.\n- Post across <span style=\"color:#3b82f6;font-weight:600\">TikTok, Instagram, Facebook, and YouTube Shorts</span> according to the plan.\n- Monitor <span style=\"color:#3b82f6;font-weight:600\">performance patterns</span> and gather insights for the next month.\n- Repeat the process monthly with improved topic selection and sharper hooks.\n\n---\n\n## 11. Rescheduling Policy\n\n- Any call, shoot, or session moved with <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">less than 24 hours notice</span> incurs a <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">$75 rescheduling fee</span>.\n- The <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">fee must be paid before rebooking</span>.\n\n---\n\n## 12. Payment, Term, and Start-of-Work Rules\n\n- <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">Do not begin</span> strategy, scripting, scheduling, or production until the <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">agreement is signed and payment is received</span>.\n- Month-to-month clients are billed at <span style=\"color:#3b82f6;font-weight:600\">$2,500</span> and remain active until canceled under the agreement terms.\n- Paid-in-full 3-month clients reserve <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">90 days of production capacity</span> and should be treated as committed production slots.\n- Unless otherwise approved in writing, <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">payments are non-refundable</span> once work has started.\n\n---\n\n## 13. Scope Boundaries and Out-of-Scope Rules\n\n- Included scope covers <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">16 short-form videos per month</span> repurposed across TikTok, Instagram, Facebook, and YouTube Shorts.\n- <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">Community management, comment replies, additional platforms, custom graphics, extra videos, platform-specific alternate edits, and reshoots</span> outside agreed scope are not included by default.\n- Any request that changes approved scripts, approved strategy, or monthly deliverable count should be <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">flagged as potential out-of-scope work</span> before action is taken.\n- Project manager must <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">document</span> any approved out-of-scope work, fee adjustments, and timeline changes in the portal.\n\n---\n\n## 14. Timeline Protection and Client Delay Rules\n\n- Turnaround timing starts only after all footage is <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">received in full and confirmed usable</span>.\n- <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">Delayed</span> client onboarding, delayed asset delivery, delayed access, delayed footage upload, and delayed approvals should <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">shift timeline expectations</span> accordingly.\n- Team should <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">document all client-caused delays</span> in the portal and note any resulting impact on scheduled posting cadence.\n- Vektiss is <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">not responsible</span> for missed publishing dates caused by client delay or missing information.\n\n---\n\n## 15. Portal Record, Access, and Approval Rules\n\n- Portal is the <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">official system of record</span> for revisions, deliverables, approvals, status updates, and project notes.\n- <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">Texts, calls, side emails, and DMs are not official</span> approval or revision channels unless copied into the portal record.\n- <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">Confirm client logins, permissions, and platform access</span> before scheduling begins; document access issues immediately.\n- Client is responsible for <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">final review of business accuracy, compliance, and approval</span> before publishing; team should not assume regulated claims are approved unless recorded by client.\n\n---\n\n## Color Key\n\n| Color | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| <span style=\"color:#22c55e;font-weight:600\">● Green</span> | Go / proceed / confirmed / included |\n| <span style=\"color:#3b82f6;font-weight:600\">● Blue</span> | Key info / action items / deliverables |\n| <span style=\"color:#f59e0b;font-weight:600\">● Amber</span> | Caution / conditions / document this |\n| <span style=\"color:#ef4444;font-weight:600\">● Red</span> | Stop / do not proceed / non-negotiable / excluded |', updated_at = now() WHERE id = 'f9bdcf8d-8910-4e0c-a7ec-92fbfa85d20b';